Remarks. The specimens agree well with published accounts: the inner and outer orbital margins are armed and carapace spination ( 8–10 : 3–5 : 13–16 ) is within the reported range (
Galil 2000
;
Ahyong & Brown 2002
;
Ahyong & Chan 2004
).

Distribution. Worldwide, from the Indo-West Pacific, eastern Pacific, western and eastern Atlantic, including New Caledonia , Australia , and New Zealand ; 212–2505 m (
Galil 2000
;
Ahyong & Galil 2006
).
